    "[...] according to which an AI system is \"a machine-based system that, for explicit or implicit objectives, infers, from the input it receives, how to generate outputs such as predictions, content, recommendations, or decisions that can influence physical or virtual environments.",
    "Different AI systems vary in their levels of autonomy and adaptiveness after deployment\".",
    "17 With this definition of AI systems in mind, we will show through some relevant examples how the multi-component analysis of risk we have considered fruitfully applies to AI-related risk.",
    "Let us start by considering the hazard component involved in the use of AI systems, which is arguably the most discussed aspect of AI-related risk.",
    "As already noted, AI systems are now increasingly employed in a number of contexts that we intuitively perceive as highly risky."
